{"id":"ward","term":"Ward","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>A prison (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 40:3\">Gen. 40:3</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 40:4\">4</a>); a watch-station (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 21:8\">Isa. 21:8</a>); a guard (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Nehemiah 13:30\">Neh. 13:30</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Genesis 40:3","Genesis 40:4","Isaiah 21:8","Nehemiah 13:30"]}